**Read the additional data set "*cia.txt*" into R. Make sure to check if there are column names, how the elements are separated and what any missing values are denoted by etc.**

`r hide("Solution")`
Make sure to double check the format of the '.txt' file before you read it in. Looking at "*cia.csv*" shows us that there are column headings, each element is separated with a tab space, any missing data is denoted by the word `"MISSING"`, and a comma is used as the decimal point.

Therefore, we can read in "*cia.txt*" using the following code.

```{r readans1.1, eval=FALSE}
cia <- read.table(file = "cia.txt", header = TRUE, sep = "\t", na.strings = "MISSING", dec = ",")
```

```{r readans1.2, echo=FALSE}
cia <- read.table(file = "Data/cia.txt", header = TRUE, sep = "\t", na.strings = "MISSING", dec = ",")
```
`r unhide()`

